To start the project using Docker, follow these steps :

1/Prerequisites:
Make sure you have Docker Desktop and the docker engine is succesfully running

2/Building Containers:

You have to build the containers first, run:
docker-compose up -d --build

3/Running Containers:

for a second use do not rebuild again, just make sure that the containers are UP, run :
docker-compose up

4/Accessing the Application:

React client: Open your web browser and go to http://localhost:3000.
Node.js server: API endpoints are accessible at http://localhost:5000.

5/ Stopping and Removing Containers:

To stop and remove the containers, run:
docker-compose down

6/building a specific service
docker-compose build <service_name>


7/Starting a sepcific service (in this case client / server / mongo)

docker-compose up -d server
docker-compose up -d client
docker-compose up -d mongo

8/Stopping and Removing a specific service:
docker-compose stop <service_name>
docker-compose rm -f <service_name>

